data.description: Updated starter home in Commerce City with a variety of amenities to keep costs manageable! Truly an amazing, modernized galley kitchen with new appliances, quartz countertops, large undermounted kitchen sink, ample cabinetry and pantry space; nicely located to a quaint dining area. The family room has a real wood fireplace as its centerpiece and the newly laid engineered flooring adds a classy touch to this home. Walk out onto your private backyard that is fenced in leading to the back alleyway. The main floor also hosts the master bedroom and bathroom. Upstairs has two good sized bedrooms and a full bathroom. The basement isn’t completely finished but does have two rooms that are ready to go once you add flooring. There is a half bathroom in the basement as well. Special amenities include a Rain Soft water softener and an owned solar panels that basically bring your electric bill to zero. As nice as this home is, it could use a little attention in the backyard and a few minor details throughout the home. No HOA! Situated minutes from Pioneer Park with ballfields, basketball courts, skate park and Paradice Island Pool. Less than a mile to Eagle Pointe Recreation Center to the west and Dick’s Sporting Good Park to the east. Close to I-270, a Walmart Supercenter, schools, places of worship, 15 to 20 min to downtown Denver or DIA.  At under $410k, this home won’t last long!
